Class FeedSynchronizationSyndicationExtension

Extends syndication specifications to enable loosely-cooperating applications to use feeds as the basis for item sharing; the bi-directional, asynchronous synchronization of new and changed items amongst two or more cross-subscribed feeds.

Syntax
[Serializable]
public class FeedSynchronizationSyndicationExtension : SyndicationExtension, ISyndicationExtension, IXmlSerializable, IComparable
Remarks

The FeedSynchronizationSyndicationExtension extends syndicated content to specify the minimum extensions necessary to enable loosely-cooperating applications to use Atom and RSS feeds as the basis for item sharing. This syndication extension conforms to the FeedSync for Atom and RSS 1.0 specification, which can be found at http://dev.live.com/feedsync/spec/.

Context

Gets or sets the FeedSynchronizationSyndicationExtensionContext object associated with this extension.

Declaration
public FeedSynchronizationSyndicationExtensionContext Context { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
FeedSynchronizationSyndicationExtensionContext

A FeedSynchronizationSyndicationExtensionContext object that contains information associated with the current syndication extension.
Remarks

The Context encapsulates all of the syndication extension information that can be retrieved or written to an extended syndication entity. Its purpose is to prevent property naming collisions between the base SyndicationExtension class and any custom properties that are defined for the custom syndication extension.
